                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7015a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                        interests</hi>
                    <note n="69" xml:id="d1203fn69">The same to Consul Simpich at Nogales.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. Department informed American refugees at Topolobampo unable return to Los
                    Mochis because there is no guard at Aguila nor at Los Tates pumping plant.
                    Colonel Escobar at Mochis asserts he <pb facs="0971" n="855" xml:id="pg_855"/>
                    can do nothing until he receives instructions from General Muñoz at San Bias. It
                    is further reported nothing has been done to assist Americans to recover
                    property in hands Carranza forces.</p>
                <p>Convey above to appropriate authorities immediately and urge them to instruct
                    General Dieguez to station guards at Aguila and Los Tates. Also request them to
                    issue orders to the end that American properties be restored to rightful
                    owners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
